148
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:42,440
And after we decided that we wanted to go,

149
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:45,600
I guess we was tired of just going with the signs.

150
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:49,000
We wanted to make a difference and just go in and set down

151
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,800
and ask for service.

152
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:53,920
When you made that decision to, young people made a decision

153
00:10:53,920 --> 00:10:59,400
to go out and do this sit in, you alluded to some

154
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:03,200
frustration with older leaders who weren't quite so ready

155
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:04,520
to take more aggressive steps.

156
00:11:04,520 --> 00:11:08,000
Can you talk a little bit about that difference in

157
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,920
perspective between the young folks and older, say,

158
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:11,400
any of these decisions?

159
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:14,720
Well, our perspective was that I guess we just wanted to go

160
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:16,320
on and sit down.

161
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:18,120
And I guess they wanted a little more time.

162
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:20,800
Maybe they wanted ready to make that plunge.

163
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:25,920
But for us, it was like we need to go and sit in and ask

164
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:27,080
for service.

165
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:28,320
So that's why we did.

166
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:32,200
And when we did, we met our adversary who said they do

167
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:34,040
not serve Niggas here.

168
00:11:34,040 --> 00:11:38,960
You would have to leave, be arrested.

169
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:40,560
We continue to set.

170
00:11:40,560 --> 00:11:42,240
At the counter, at the counter.

171
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:47,200
And they said, we tell you if you don't leave, because we

172
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:49,480
